div.div:
EF Core 5’s direct many-to-many relationship works because (a) EF Core
creates the linking entity class for you and (b) when it sees a query containing a direct
many-to-many relationship, it adds the SQL commands to use the hidden linking entity
class. Not having to create the linking entity class or perform configuration makes
these sorts of many-to-many relationships much easier to set up.
